frameDefinitions: An Entity undergoes some change (the Event) that is (or is construed as) punctual.
An Entity is affected by an Event.
In this frame an Experiencer experiences an Emotion or is in an Emotional_state.
Words in this frame have to do with a Cognizer adding some Phenomenon to their model of the world.
A Competitor claims a Prize as a result of the outcome of their participation in a Competition.
frameExamples: This <t>happens</t> to me all the time.
The hotel is <t>undergoing</t> renovations at this time.
Later that night, they <t>found</t> the barely-alive victim inside the Red Hall estate flat.
We <t>won</t> a car in the raffle.
listRoleDefinitions: This role identifies the entity, concrete or abstract.
This role identifies the time when the event occurs.
This role identifies where the event takes place.
The thing which is affected by the Event.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the <fen>Entity</fen> undergoes the <fen>Event</fen>.
The location at which the <fen>Entity</fen> undergoes the <fen>Event</fen>.
The <fen>Experiencer</fen> experiences the <fen>Emotion</fen> or is in the <fen>Emotional_state</fen>.
The <fen>Emotion</fen> is the feeling that the <fen>Experiencer</fen> experiences.
The <fen>Emotional_state</fen> is the state the <fen>Experiencer</fen> is in.
The <fen>Evaluation</fen> is a negative or positive assessment of the <fen>Experiencer</fen> regarding his or her <fen>Emotional_state</fen>.
The <fen>Cognizer</fen> is the person who becomes aware of a <fen>Phenomenon</fen>. It is normally expressed as an External Argument.
Thm <fen>Phenomenon</fen> is the entity or situation in the world of which a <fen>Cognizer</fen> becomes aware. It is normally expressed as an Object:
This role identifes the <fen>Means</fen> by which the <fen>Cognizer</fen> becomes aware of the <fen>Phenomenon</fen>.
<fen>Topic</fen> indicates the general field within which the <fen>Phenomenon</fen> is found.
The <fen>Cognizer</fen> uses an <fen>Instrument</fen> to (enable themselves to) become aware of the <fen>Phenomenon</fen>.  In some cases, the <fen>Instrument</fen> may appear in subject position.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Cognizer</fen> becomes aware of the <fen>Phenomenon</fen>.
The individual or individuals involved in the <fen>Competition</fen>.
A socially and/or monetarily significant entity which is given to a <fen>Competitor</fen> according to <fen>Score</fen> or <fen>Rank</fen>.
When the <fen>Competition</fen> takes place.
The location where the <fen>Competition</fen> takes place.
listRoleExamples: After two pints, <fex>he</fex> felt a bit better and Ted arrived.
Patients experience <fex>high anxiety levels</fex> at time of admission to hospital.
Her heart was galloping so fast that she felt <fex>quite giddy with happiness</fex>.
Max was feeling <fex>worse than he'd ever felt in his life</fex>.
<fex>Pat</fex> discovered a great little restaurant in Soho.
Pat discovered <fex>a great little restaurant</fex> in Soho.
<fex>By opening the book to page 10</fex>, you will find the Van Eerdens' number.
Scientists attempt to make discoveries <fex>about the laws of nature</fex>.
Olson says the deputy came out to the farm and detected a radioactive substance <fex>with his Geiger counter</fex>.
Robbie had wondered if they would be able to find the path <fex>at night</fex>.
